00:28:44.080 --> 00:28:46.071
- What are you doing?
- I'm having fun.

00:28:46.240 --> 00:28:48.390
What, discussing the pigeon with Bob?

00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:50.951
Hailey has so gotten under your skin.

00:28:51.120 --> 00:28:53.873
- No. This is not about Hailey.
- Oh, no?

00:28:54.040 --> 00:28:56.713
No. Maybe we needed to do this.

00:28:56.880 --> 00:28:58.632
Maybe we need to do
something dangerous.

00:28:58.800 --> 00:29:02.236
Maybe we are in a rut,
and we didn't even know it.

00:29:02.400 --> 00:29:05.551
- So you want to swing?
- I'm swinging.

00:29:07.240 --> 00:29:08.912
Heidi.

00:29:09.080 --> 00:29:11.958
You have got to finish telling me
about the Galapagos Islands.

00:29:12.120 --> 00:29:13.519
What a wild place.

00:29:14.640 --> 00:29:16.790
Forty-five minutes to midnight.

00:29:17.680 --> 00:29:20.797
If I ever get out of here,
your aunt is dead.

00:29:23.200 --> 00:29:25.668
- Hey, Ryan.
- Yeah?

00:29:26.040 --> 00:29:29.157
I have to ask you.
Why didn't you just say it?

00:29:29.600 --> 00:29:31.113
I don't know.

00:29:34.040 --> 00:29:35.758
Because I never have.

00:29:36.320 --> 00:29:37.594
But you do, right?

00:29:38.040 --> 00:29:40.315
I guess. I don't know.

00:29:41.200 --> 00:29:43.031
How do you know?

00:29:43.200 --> 00:29:45.589
I just think you know. I don't know.

00:29:47.840 --> 00:29:49.796
Yeah, I do.

00:29:52.960 --> 00:29:56.635
Why didn't you choose? I mean, you had
to like one more than the other, right?

00:30:01.760 --> 00:30:03.910
But now I don't deserve either,
because I blew it.

00:30:04.080 --> 00:30:05.752
Me too.

00:30:06.680 --> 00:30:09.478
I'm optimistic about this
Friendster thing, though.

00:30:09.640 --> 00:30:10.959
Forty-three minutes.

00:30:17.160 --> 00:30:18.388
- Hi.
- Hailey...

00:30:18.560 --> 00:30:21.677
...mad good party once again.
- Thanks for coming.

00:30:21.840 --> 00:30:23.159
Happy New Year.

00:30:24.800 --> 00:30:28.475
Where is that bitch? I can't believe
she'd even show her face in Newport.

00:30:28.640 --> 00:30:30.358
Cami, I don't know, okay?

00:30:44.840 --> 00:30:47.479
- I need help.
- Fresh oxygen.

00:30:47.680 --> 00:30:50.240
So you locked us in,
and now you want our help?

00:30:50.960 --> 00:30:52.791
- Pretty much, yes.
- No. I'm leaving.

00:30:52.960 --> 00:30:55.269
Wait, there's a girl out there
that wants to kill me.

00:30:55.440 --> 00:30:56.509
Just one?

00:30:56.680 --> 00:30:59.638
There's a girl who will kill me
if I don't get there in 39 minutes.

00:30:59.800 --> 00:31:02.598
- Okay, but please help me shut this down.
- I'm not helping you.

00:31:02.760 --> 00:31:05.194
Fine. Then she's gonna tear
this house apart.

00:31:07.560 --> 00:31:09.118
Do it for Sandy and Kirsten.

00:31:09.440 --> 00:31:11.237
Let's go. We gotta clear this party out.

00:31:11.400 --> 00:31:12.992
It's what I do best.

00:31:18.280 --> 00:31:21.078
- Good night.
- Thanks for coming.

00:31:23.160 --> 00:31:24.718
What did you do?

00:31:24.880 --> 00:31:27.997
- We shut off the power.
- Told them the cops were coming.

00:31:28.680 --> 00:31:30.477
- I gotta go.
- Go ahead. I'll clean up.

00:31:30.640 --> 00:31:31.993
- You sure?
- Yes. Go.

00:31:32.160 --> 00:31:34.071
Thirty-one minutes.
I hope I can make it.

00:31:34.240 --> 00:31:35.468
Me too.

00:31:47.240 --> 00:31:49.231
Come on, everybody. It's 11:30.

00:31:49.400 --> 00:31:50.879
We need to make our selection...

00:31:51.040 --> 00:31:54.669
...so we have someone new to ring
in the new year with.

00:31:57.760 --> 00:32:02.470
Since this is Evelyn's house,
we'll let her pick first. Evie?

00:32:08.960 --> 00:32:10.791
Way to go, Bob.

00:32:36.080 --> 00:32:37.115
Okay.

00:32:47.520 --> 00:32:50.398
I hope you have some better luck.

00:33:12.240 --> 00:33:14.356
I don't get it.

00:33:14.520 --> 00:33:18.229
Everyone else got picked.
What happened to my watch?

00:33:18.520 --> 00:33:20.636
It better be in your pants.

00:33:27.760 --> 00:33:29.557
Come on, swinger.

00:33:29.720 --> 00:33:31.039
Let's go home.

00:33:33.640 --> 00:33:35.835
<i>Traffic is looking pretty bad</i>
<i>on the 73.</i>

00:33:36.000 --> 00:33:40.437
<i>New Year's Eve is always ugly</i>
<i>on the road. Luckily it's almost over.</i>

00:34:03.160 --> 00:34:05.958
Hey. I'm gonna take off.

00:34:06.120 --> 00:34:08.111
You are? So close to midnight?

00:34:08.280 --> 00:34:11.795
Yeah, yeah. I don't wanna be here.
It's too depressing.

00:34:13.000 --> 00:34:15.070
- Happy New Year.
- Thanks.

00:34:19.440 --> 00:34:21.908
Hey. How you doing?

00:34:22.080 --> 00:34:26.198
I know it sounds stupid, but I keep
looking back at the door thinking...

00:34:26.360 --> 00:34:28.999
...maybe he'll show up...

00:34:29.560 --> 00:34:30.549
...in time.

00:34:31.040 --> 00:34:33.554
Yeah. I keep hoping to see Natalie.

00:34:33.840 --> 00:34:35.512
Sadly, I think it's just us tonight.

00:34:37.240 --> 00:34:39.356
But, hey, at least we have each other.

00:34:53.400 --> 00:34:55.960
- I think we're in the wrong house.
- I don't.

00:34:57.040 --> 00:34:58.029
What the hell happened?

00:34:58.200 --> 00:35:00.555
I don't know enough people
to cause this much damage.

00:35:00.720 --> 00:35:02.836
So how was the party?

00:35:03.200 --> 00:35:05.555
- What did you do?
- Nothing that can't be undone.

00:35:05.720 --> 00:35:08.837
A little Palmolive, some elbow grease.
Seth and I have it covered.

00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:10.592
Nobody mentioned elbow grease.

00:35:10.760 --> 00:35:13.069
Seth. Garbage. Out. Now.

00:35:15.720 --> 00:35:19.076
I look forward to waking up
to a clean house tomorrow.

00:35:21.000 --> 00:35:22.513
Good night, Sandy.

00:35:23.080 --> 00:35:24.559
I'm gonna get back to the dishes.

00:35:24.720 --> 00:35:26.472
You don't walk away from me.

00:35:26.640 --> 00:35:29.677
You're not Mom.
You can't talk to me that way.

00:35:29.840 --> 00:35:33.276
This is my house,
my upside-down couch!

00:35:33.440 --> 00:35:36.193
I will talk to you any way that I want.

00:35:42.160 --> 00:35:44.151
I should really learn to knock...

00:35:46.240 --> 00:35:49.516
...in case there's a threesome
going on in my bedroom.

00:35:51.440 --> 00:35:54.796
You can't keep living your life like this,
like you have no responsibility.

00:35:54.960 --> 00:35:56.279
Like you're still a child.

00:35:56.440 --> 00:35:58.715
What used to be cute
is now embarrassing.

00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:01.519
I'm sorry. The party got
a little out of hand.

00:36:01.680 --> 00:36:03.511
People your age,
they have finished college...

00:36:03.680 --> 00:36:05.716
...they have jobs, they're married.

00:36:05.880 --> 00:36:08.713
Look. In the morning I'll take off.

00:36:08.880 --> 00:36:12.077
I am not asking you to leave.
I just want you to grow up!

00:36:20.440 --> 00:36:23.432
It's a new year.
You can make a new start.

00:36:24.240 --> 00:36:27.277
Why? So I can grow up
to be just like you?

00:36:27.440 --> 00:36:29.510
Working for Dad,
selling McMansions...

00:36:29.680 --> 00:36:31.557
...planning charity events
with the Newpsies?

00:36:31.720 --> 00:36:34.188
Hey. I love my life...

00:36:34.360 --> 00:36:36.555
...my family, my rut.

00:36:38.640 --> 00:36:40.710
You spend so much time...

00:36:40.880 --> 00:36:45.192
...putting energy into having fun,
your whole life is dedicated to having fun.

00:36:46.480 --> 00:36:48.391
Are you even having any?

00:36:51.840 --> 00:36:54.673
- I'll help you clean up.
- I don't want your help.

00:36:56.760 --> 00:36:59.957
I'll finish in the morning.
I'm going to bed.

00:37:07.920 --> 00:37:09.558
Anna? Hey.

00:37:10.480 --> 00:37:12.755
I didn't want you to be alone
on New Year's.

00:37:14.320 --> 00:37:15.992
Actually...

00:37:17.240 --> 00:37:18.958
I didn't want to be alone
on New Year's.

00:37:20.080 --> 00:37:21.832
Well, I'm not alone.

00:37:22.520 --> 00:37:24.511
I have Captain Oats
and Carson Daly, so...

00:37:24.680 --> 00:37:28.468
Oh, wow. That's an unbeatable
combination. I'll go.

00:37:28.640 --> 00:37:32.235
Wait. Captain Oats
had too much champagne...

00:37:32.400 --> 00:37:35.472
...and Carson Daly's
kind of a ginormous tool.

00:37:36.040 --> 00:37:37.393
So I could use the company.

00:38:18.800 --> 00:38:20.279
Twenty seconds.

00:38:32.160 --> 00:38:34.799
Ten. Nine. Eight.

00:38:34.960 --> 00:38:37.679
Seven. Six. Five.

00:40:03.480 --> 00:40:05.357
You're not Seth Cohen.

00:40:05.520 --> 00:40:07.351
Who's Seth Cohen?

00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:10.475
I wasn't... I wasn't talking to you.

00:40:11.600 --> 00:40:13.477
I gotta go.

00:40:13.640 --> 00:40:15.551
Happy New Year.

00:40:22.400 --> 00:40:24.914
- I love you.
- What?

00:40:25.920 --> 00:40:27.273
I love you.

00:40:31.720 --> 00:40:33.358
Thank you.

00:00:0.500 --> 00:00:2.00
